The paper discusses the application of SMT solvers to verify embedded software written in ANSI-C, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of encodings for finite variables, bit-vector operations, arrays, structures, unions, and pointers, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the limitations of propositional bounded model checking and the need for richer theories, which are related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the evaluation of the approach on embedded applications from telecommunications, control systems, and medical devices, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.EM).
